$string['detail_method_balance'] = 'Activity balance is measured by categorising all LMS log events from the past 30 days into four categories based on Dawson\'s (2006) framework: Engagement (forums, wikis, glossaries, workshops, databases, chats), Content (pages, books, resources, URLs, folders, labels, H5P), Assessment (assignments, quizzes, lessons, SCORM, feedback activities), and Administration (all other LMS actions). The percentage distribution across these categories is calculated for the entire cohort.';
$string['detail_method_compound'] = 'This indicator cross-references two independent data sources: social presence (forum participation rate) and academic performance (course grade percentage). Each student\'s forum participation rate is calculated as the proportion of course discussions they have contributed to. Their grade is their current course total. A student is flagged when both indicators fall below their respective thresholds simultaneously.';
$string['detail_method_engagement'] = 'Course engagement is measured by counting how many distinct trackable activities each student has interacted with. This includes: assignments submitted and graded, quiz attempts completed, and course resources viewed (pages, books, files, URLs, folders — tracked via Moodle\'s log store). The engagement rate is the proportion of total trackable activities the student has engaged with.';
$string['detail_method_failing'] = 'This indicator uses each student\'s current course total grade, expressed as a percentage of the maximum possible grade. The course total is calculated by Moodle\'s gradebook using the aggregation method configured for the course (e.g., weighted mean, natural). Students below the pass mark threshold are counted and expressed as a proportion of the cohort.';
$string['detail_method_feedback'] = 'Teaching presence is measured through feedback engagement. For each student, we count the number of graded assignments where the teacher has provided a grade, and then check Moodle\'s log store for events indicating the student viewed their feedback (feedback_viewed or submission_status_viewed events). The feedback review rate is the proportion of graded items for which the student has viewed the feedback.';
$string['detail_method_isolation'] = 'Social presence is measured through forum participation. For each student, we count the number of distinct course discussion threads they have posted in. The participation rate is calculated as the proportion of total course discussions the student has contributed to. Students are classified into five levels (Not started, Emerging, Developing, Established, Exemplary) based on this rate. Students at "Not started" or "Emerging" are flagged as having low social presence.';
$string['detail_method_stale'] = 'This indicator checks each student\'s most recent forum post timestamp. Students who have previously participated in forums (at least one post) but have not posted again within the inactivity window are flagged. The average days inactive is calculated across all flagged students. This detects disengagement patterns distinct from students who have never participated.';
$string['detail_metric_activitylist'] = 'Assignments, quizzes, pages, books, resources, URLs, folders';
